trid.file_type: Mac OS X Mach-O universal Dynamically linked shared Library

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the execution of "system_profiler" with specific "Data Types" that have been seen being used by threat actors and malware. It provides system hardware and software configuration information.
This process is primarily used for system information discovery. However, "system_profiler" can also be used to determine if virtualization software is being run for defense evasion purposes.
Detects execution of AppleScript of the macOS scripting language AppleScript.

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=/usr/bin/osascript osascript -e tell application 'Terminal' to set visible of front window to false; Image=/usr/bin/osascript; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=/usr/bin/osascript osascript -e display dialog 'To launch the application, you need to update the system settings \n\nPlease enter your password.' with title 'System Preferences' with icon caution default answer '' giving up after 30 with hidden answer; Image=/usr/bin/osascript; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine=/usr/bin/osascript osascript -e display dialog 'To launch the application, you need to update the system settings You entered an invalid password.\n\nPlease enter your password.' with title 'System Preferences' with icon caution default answer '' giving up after 30 with hidden answer; Image=/usr/bin/osascript; EventID=1}

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: APP-DETECT Apple Messages push.apple.com DNS TXT request attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert udp $HOME_NET any -> any 53 ( msg:"APP-DETECT Apple Messages push.apple.com DNS TXT request attempt"; flow:to_server; byte_test:1,!&,0xF8,2; content:"|04|push|05|apple|03|com|00 00 10 00 01|",fast_pattern,nocase; service:dns; reference:url,www.apple.com/osx/apps/all.html#messages; classtype:policy-violation; gid:1; sid:25080; rev:3; )

attributes.magic: Mach-O universal binary with 2 architectures: [\012- x86_64:\012- Mach-O 64-bit x86_64 executable, flags:<NOUNDEFS|DYLDLINK|TWOLEVEL|WEAK_DEFINES|BINDS_TO_WEAK|PIE>] [\012- arm64:\012- Mach-O 64-bit arm64 executable, flags:<NOUNDEFS|DYLDLINK|TWOLEVEL|BINDS_TO_WEAK|PIE>]

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a multi-component malware that functions as an information stealer and trojanizer, primarily targeting cryptocurrency assets. It systematically searches for and exfiltrates sensitive data from various web browsers (e.g., Chrome, Firefox, Vivaldi) and a wide range of cryptocurrency wallets (e.g., Exodus, Electrum, Coinomi, Guarda, Atomic, Ledger Live). The malware also contains functionality to trojanize the legitimate Ledger Live application by replacing its components, likely to steal credentials or manipulate transactions. Exfiltration is attempted to a C2 server via an obfuscated URL. It also uses `osascript` for social engineering and `xattr` to remove the quarantine attribute, bypassing Gatekeeper.
